author: AccessWDUN staff
title: Volleyball: Lady Dragons set new wins mark, clinch No. 2 seed in 8-AAA
text:
By AccessWDUN staff Related Articles Volleyball: East Hall gets sweep at Madison County Volleyball: Gainesville closes out season with sweep of 8- matches Volleyball: GHS drops pair of matches Volleyball: Gainesville clinches two region wins 
JEFFERSON — The Jefferson girls volleyball team swept a pair of matches in battle of Jackson County teams on Thursday. 
The Lady Dragons whipped Jackson County 25-5, 25-9 and then held off East Jackson 25-16, 25-21 victory over East Jackson. With the victories, the Lady Dragons ran their record to a new school-record in wins at 32-5 and they clinched the No. 2 seed in the upcoming Area 8-AAA Tournament. 
Jefferson will play host to Nos. 3 and 6 seeds next Thursday in the Area Tournament and then will play the winner of that match.
